Query String in Django:
A query string is the part of a URL that starts with "?" and contains data as key-value pairs. Django provides access to query string parameters through request.GET.

Example:
URL: /search/?q=python&page=2

View:
def search(request):
    query = request.GET.get("q")
    page = request.GET.get("page")

Template:
<a href="/profile/?user_id={{ user.id }}">View Profile</a>

Uses:
- filtering data
- pagination
- sorting
- searching
- passing non-sensitive parameters via URL
